<TITLE> Banks may stay open Saturday: BB </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 17 (bdnews24.com)Bangladesh Bank has announced that individual banks and branches may stay open for business on Saturday, which would be the last banking day before the Eid holiday. The circular was sent to the chief executives of all banks on Thursday. "Ahead of upcoming Eid-ul-Fitr, banks will be able to keep all their branches or some specific branches open on September 19, on their own consideration of their customers' needs by and ensuring proper security," the central bank said. The circular specifically asked bank branches of all ports (sea, air and land) to stay open on Friday and Saturday to facilitate international trade. It also said bank authorities can decide to keep other bank branches dealing with foreign exchange open on Saturday, if needed. bdn
